[1] Case updates
- Sat 12 Jan 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=922767f361

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 11 Jan 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 634, of which 586 are confirmed and 48 are probable. In total, there were 386 deaths (338 confirmed and 48 probable) and 231 people recovered.
- 121 suspected cases under investigation.
- 2 new confirmed cases, including 1 in Katwa and 1 in Komanda.
- No new confirmed case deaths reported this day.
- 4 new recoveries released from Butembo ETC.

News of the response
Vaccination
-----------
- Since the start of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 58 956 people have been vaccinated , including 19 855 in Beni [North Kivu], 12 153 in Katwa [North Kivu], 6746 in Butembo [North Kivu], 5686 in Mabalako [North Kivu], 2283 in Kalunguta [North Kivu], 1774 in Komanda [Ituri], 1663 in Mandima [Ituri], 1435 in Goma [North Kivu], 1272 in Oicha [North Kivu], 854 in Karisimbi [North Kivu], 791 in Vuhovi [North Kivu], 750 in Masereka [North Kivu], 735 in Kyondo [North Kivu], 700 in Lubero [North Kivu], 599 in Mutwanga [North Kivu], 434 in Bunia [Ituri], 394 in Musienene [North Kivu], 355 in Tchomia [Ituri], 167 in Nyankunde [Ituri], 120 in Biena [North Kivu], 63 in Alimbongo [North Kivu], 54 in Nyiragongo [North Kivu], and 13 in Kisangani [Tshopo].

- The only vaccine to be used in this outbreak is the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, manufactured by the pharmaceutical group Merck, following approval by the Ethics Committee in its decision of 19 May 2018.

--
