The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 10 Jan 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 632, of which 584 are confirmed and 48 are probable. In total, there were 386 deaths (338 confirmed and 48 probable) and 227 people cured.
- 58 suspected cases under investigation.
- 2 new confirmed cases, including 1 in Oicha and 1 in Vuhovi.
- 1 new death of a confirmed case at Butembo ETC.
- 1 new recovery released from Katwa ETC.

